{"tid":1976922,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"美國太空戰隊Target開戰時立即將俄羅斯同中國既人造衛星癱瘓","createTime":"2020-04-17T14:42:18.000Z","updateTime":"2020-04-18T04:51:22.000Z","uid":104138,"like":54,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":30,"replies":[{"pid":"f10ba88010482f0da74de9d5d53c9d289bfff2d4","tid":1976922,"uid":104138,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-17T14:42:18.000Z","msg":"<strong>U.S. Space Force Is Arming to Jam Russian and Chinese Satellites</strong><br />\n<br />\nThe new U.S. Space Force is building an arsenal of as many as 48 ground-based weapons over the next seven years designed to temporarily jam Russian or Chinese communications satellite signals in the opening hours of a conflict.<br />\n<br />\nThe first system, made by L3Harris Technologies Inc., was declared operational last month after years of development, and the Space Force has taken delivery of 16 of them. The service is also developing a new system, known as Meadowland, that&rsquo;s lighter-weight, capable of adding updated software and able to jam more frequencies.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-17/u-s-space-force-is-arming-to-jam-russian-and-chinese-satellites\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2020-04-17%2Fu-s-space-force-is-arming-to-jam-russian-and-chinese-satellites&d=5Vq0xNKZ3qFPdYugipJU9%2FkXgXr6FxeO6pMo8RORPdo%3D&h=5d4716b9\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-17/u-s-space-force-is-arming-to-jam-russian-and-chinese-satellites</a>"},{"pid":"60220529c06db57b058ed73e468c124ecf085387","tid":1976922,"uid":1655,"like":7,"dislike":0,"score":7,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-17T14:43:01.000Z","msg":"Ace Combat 7<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"6d6c98ebf2fc9d1ce396a106b07efb6a9afa0a68","tid":1976922,"uid":177213,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-17T14:43:19.000Z","msg"